No, I don\'t.\" \"How could you?\" she admitted. \"Luck was with you, friend. When you startled the beast, it fled, but it could just as easily have killed you with a wink or a sneeze.\" She approached me, and as she did, it became apparent that she was barely half my height. She held out one of her calloused hands, which I accepted and shook. \"Aeri Goldmane,\" she said, introducing herself. \"On account of my hair.\" Her hand instinctively went up, combing through her tangled locks.")
